data.name: CtorAnalyserTitle
data.value: CtorSet should only be used in specific circumstances

data.name: CtorBridgeAttributeMessageFormat
data.value: CtorSet's propertyRetriever lambda must directly indicate an instance property that has no Bridge attributes on the getter or setter

data.name: CtorDirectPropertyTargetAccessorArgumentMessageFormat
data.value: CtorSet's propertyRetriever lambda must directly indicate an instance property with a getter and a setter (which may be private) or that is a readonly auto-property

data.name: CtorMayOnlyBeCalledWithConstructorMessageFormat
data.value: CtorSet should only be called within a constructor

data.name: CtorSimpleMemberAccessRuleMessageFormat
data.value: CtorSet must be a simple member access expression that targets "this" - it must be of the form this.CtorSet(..)

data.name: CtorSimplePropertyAccessorArgumentMessageFormat
data.value: CtorSet's propertyRetriever lambda must directly indicate an instance property with a getter and a setter (which may be private) or that is a readonly auto-property

data.name: GetPropertyAnalyserTitle
data.value: GetProperty should only be used in a particular manner

data.name: GetPropertyBridgeAttributeMessageFormat
data.value: GetProperty's propertyRetriever lambda must directly indicate an instance property that has no Bridge attributes on the getter or setter

data.name: GetPropertyDirectPropertyTargetAccessorArgumentMessageFormat
data.value: GetProperty's propertyRetriever lambda's target must be a direct access and may not include any casts or other indirection

data.name: GetPropertySimplePropertyAccessorArgumentMessageFormat
data.value: GetProperty's propertyRetriever lambda must directly indicate an instance property with a getter and a setter (which may be private) or that is a readonly auto-property

data.name: IAmImmutableAnalyserTitle
data.value: Properties on IAmImmutable must follow prescribed guidelines

data.name: IAmImmutableAutoPopulatorAnalyserEmptyConstructorMessageFormat
data.value: IAmImmutable implementation '{0}' has an empty constructor that may be used to populate the class

data.name: IAmImmutableAutoPopulatorAnalyserOutOfSyncConstructorMessageFormat
data.value: IAmImmutable implementation '{0}' has constructor argument(s) that are not used to set properties: {1}

data.name: IAmImmutableAutoPopulatorAnalyserTitle
data.value: IAmImmutable implementation may be auto-generated

data.name: IAmImmutableFieldsMayNotBePublicAndMutableMessageFormat
data.value: IAmImmutable implementations may not have non-readonly public fields (such as {0})

data.name: IAmImmutablePropertiesMayNotHavePublicSetterMessageFormat
data.value: The setter on property '{0}' must be private as it is on a class that implements IAmImmutable

data.name: IAmImmutablePropertiesMustHaveSettersMessageFormat
data.value: Property '{0}' must have a setter since it has a getter and is on a class that implements IAmImmutable

data.name: IAmImmutablePropertiesMustNotHaveBridgeAttributesMessageFormat
data.value: May not have Bridge attributes on properties with getters ({0}) on classes that implement IAmImmutable

data.name: IAmImmutableValidationShouldNotBePerformedInConstructor
data.value: When new IAmImmutable instances are created via "With" calls, the constructor is not called and so any validation there will be bypassed. If parameter validation is required then you may add a "Validate" method to the class and call it at the end of the constructor, it will also be called whenever "With"creates a new instance. The "Validate" method must have no parameters and must not be decorated with any Bridge attributes (it is acceptable for the method to be private).

data.name: MethodParameterWithoutPropertyIdentifierAttribute
data.value: The propertyRetriever must be a simple in-place property-accessing lambda or a PropertyIdentifier<T, TPropertyValue> instance or a method argument with a [PropertyIdentifier] attribute - here it is a method argument that is a delegate type but without a [PropertyIdentifier] attribute, did you forget to add it?

data.name: PropertyIdentifierAttributeAnalyserTitle
data.value: [PropertyIdentifier] arguments must follow prescribed guidelines

data.name: PropertyIdentifierAttributeBridgeAttributeMessageFormat
data.value: [PropertyIdentifier] argument lambdas must directly indicate an instance property that has no Bridge attributes on the getter or setter

data.name: PropertyIdentifierAttributeDirectPropertyTargetAccessorArgumentMessageFormat
data.value: [PropertyIdentifier] argument lambdas' targets must be direct accesses and may not include any casts or other indirection

data.name: PropertyIdentifierAttributeInvalidDelegateMessageFormat
data.value: [PropertyIdentifier] arguments must be a delegate that takes a single source reference and returns a property value from it (so it must be a two-argument delegate type)

data.name: PropertyIdentifierAttributeReassignmentMessageFormat
data.value: [PropertyIdentifier] arguments may not be reassigned (they may not be set directly to a new value and they may not be used to provide a ref or out argument in a method call)

data.name: PropertyIdentifierAttributeSimplePropertyAccessorArgumentMessageFormat
data.value: [PropertyIdentifier] argument lambdas must directly indicate an instance property with a getter and a setter (which may be private) or that is a readonly auto-property

data.name: PropertyIdentifierAttributeTargetTypeNotSpecificEnoughMessageFormat
data.value: The target type of the delegate is not specific enough - the specified property is of type "{0}" and so the delegate return type must be this type or one derived from it (which "{1}" is not)

data.name: TPropertyValueNotSpecificEnough
data.value: TPropertyValue is a type that is less specialised than the indicated property - the specified property is of type "{0}" and so the type of the value that will be used to update the property must be this type or one derived from it (which "{1}" is not)

data.name: WithAnalyserTitle
data.value: With should only be used in a particular manner

data.name: WithBridgeAttributeMessageFormat
data.value: With's propertyRetriever lambda must directly indicate an instance property that has no Bridge attributes on the getter or setter

data.name: WithDirectPropertyTargetAccessorArgumentMessageFormat
data.value: With's propertyRetriever lambda's target must be a direct access and may not include any casts or other indirection

data.name: WithSimplePropertyAccessorArgumentMessageFormat
data.value: With's propertyRetriever lambda must directly indicate an instance property with a getter and a setter (which may be private) or that is a readonly auto-property
